# .trivyignore — Accepted CVEs for the build container
#
# This file lists CVEs that have been reviewed and accepted as low-risk
# for this build-only container image. The image is never deployed to
# production — it is used solely for cross-compilation.
#
# Review this file periodically. Remove entries when upstream fixes land.
#
# Format: one CVE ID per line. Lines starting with # are comments.
# See: https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/#by-finding-ids

# zlib1g — integer overflow in zipOpenNewFileInZip4_64.
# Affects minizip's zip-creation API, which this container does not use.
# Debian marks will_not_fix (minizip component, not core zlib decompression).
CVE-2023-45853

# linux-libc-dev — kernel GEM memory exhaustion (2013).
# Build container only uses kernel headers for cross-compilation; no GEM
# graphics subsystem is loaded or exercised. Debian marks will_not_fix.
CVE-2013-7445

